data.title: Répertoire pour "Sports Personalities"
data.text:
Marat Safin

This Russian tennis player doesn’t speak too much about his place of residence. In 2015, Marat reportedly felt compelled to rent a hotel during the Rolex Masters tournament, although at that time he already had an apartment in the Principality. […]

Max Verstappen

Racing driver for Red Bull, Max Verstappen comes from a family of race car drivers. His mother competed in karting tournaments and his father, Jos Verstappen, competed in F1 from 1994 to 2003. At 17, he became the youngest race-car […]

Mika Häkkinen

The two-time Formula 1 champion participated in races from 1991 to 2001. Apparently, it is during this time that his love for Monaco began, as he was competing on one of the most prestigious F1 tracks. Despite the fact that […]

Miloš Raonic

Milos Raonic was born on 27 December 1990 in Titograd, Yugoslavia (now Podgorica in Montenegro). A Canadian tennis player of Montenegrin origin, he turned professional in 2008. He has won eight singles tournaments on the ATP Tour and his best […]

Nico Hulkenberg

Nicolas, known as “Nico” Hülkenberg, was born on 19 August 1987 in Emmerich am Rhein, North Rhine-Westphalia (Germany). Winner of the Formula 3 Euro Series championship in 2008 and the GP2 Series championship in 2009, he made his Formula 1 […]

Nico Rosberg

The German-Finnish driver competed for the Williams team (2006-2009) before joining the Mercedes Petronas team (2010-2016). He has won the Monaco Grand Prix three times. He holds 15 Grand Prix victories. In December 2016, at the peak of his career […]

Novak Djokovic

Novak settled in Monaco years ago. Here he opened his only one vegan restaurant Eqvita in Monaco, which was located on Rue de Portier and received many positive client reviews. But unfortunately, now its closed. The Serbian tennis player is […]

Petra Kvitová

Petra Kvitová is a Czech tennis player born on 8 March 1990 in Bílovec. Renowned for the quality of her serve and forehand, she became well known after reaching the semi-finals of the 2010 Wimbledon tournament, where she lost to […]

Radek Stepanek

Radek Štěpánek, born November 27, 1978 (age 42) in Karviná, is a Czech tennis player, professional from 1996 to 2017. In 2004, he reached the final of the Paris-Bercy Masters. In Grand Slams, he reached the quarter-finals at Wimbledon in […]

Sergey Bubka

Sergueï Bubkanote is a Ukrainian athlete, specialist in pole vaulting, born on December 4, 1963 in Luhansk in the USSR (today in Ukraine). He was named Hero of Ukraine by President Leonid Kuchma on 4 February 20011. He competed in […]

Thierry Boutsen

Thierry Marc Boutsen, born on 13 July 1957 in Brussels, is a former French-speaking Belgian racing driver, having won several Formula 1 and endurance races. Thierry Boutsen made his Formula 1 debut with the British team Arrows in 1983. He […]

Thierry Boutsen

The Belgian racing driver Thierry Boutsen began his career in Formula 1 in 1983 and spent 10 years on the track. Monaco did not leave the pilot indifferent, and Thierry moved to the Principality. Here he launched his own company, […]

Tomáš Berdych

Tomáš Berdych was born on 17 September 1985 in Valašské Meziříčí. He is a Czech tennis player, who was a professional between 2002 and 2019. He won thirteen singles titles on the ATP circuit, including the Masters 1000 at Paris-Bercy […]

Valtteri Bottas

Valtteri Bottas was born on 28 August 1989 in Nastola, Finland. A winner of the 2011 GP3 Series Championship, he made his Formula 1 debut in 2013 with the Williams team and achieved his first podium finish the following year. […]
